    "title": "Commands: the Imperative",
    "explanation": "Regarde ! Prends l'arme ! — no subject pronoun. When giving a command, the subject disappears. Just the verb, alone.\n\nNotice the exclamation marks. Regarde ! (Look!) vs. Il regarde (He looks). Same verb, different form.\n\nRe-read and find every command. Who is being spoken to? How do commands look different from statements?"
